<span id="freeTextContainer8753914811152096147"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1472750173i/20237706._SX540_.jpg' width='200' height='150' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>*2.5 stars*<br/><br/>Underwhelming from <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14032.Connie_Willis' title='Connie Willis' rel='nofollow noopener'>Connie Willis</a>, one of my long-time favorite authors. This book is less sci-fi (in fact, I didn&apos;t even shelve it as such), and more realistic fiction or speculative fiction, or even romantic comedy. <br/><br/>It&apos;s really hard to describe this book. It is sort of a rambling narrative about trends (actually pretty interesting), interpersonal relationships, and office environments with some chick-lit thrown in. It is a weird mix, and though I had no problem listening to it (due t</span>
  <span id="freeText8753914811152096147" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1472750173i/20237706._SX540_.jpg" width="200" height="150" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>*2.5 stars*<br><br>Underwhelming from <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14032.Connie_Willis" title="Connie Willis" rel="nofollow noopener">Connie Willis</a>, one of my long-time favorite authors. This book is less sci-fi (in fact, I didn't even shelve it as such), and more realistic fiction or speculative fiction, or even romantic comedy. <br><br>It's really hard to describe this book. It is sort of a rambling narrative about trends (actually pretty interesting), interpersonal relationships, and office environments with some chick-lit thrown in. It is a weird mix, and though I had no problem listening to it (due to an always great narration by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/494654.Kate_Reading" title="Kate Reading" rel="nofollow noopener">Kate Reading</a>), it was oddly dissatisfying. <br><br>I like other <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14032.Connie_Willis" title="Connie Willis" rel="nofollow noopener">Connie Willis</a> books much more. </span>
